column215: I think Minesweeper is not as intuitive of a game as the others for someone who has never played it

The final images of the map were a bit unclear and surprising as the concept of maps and paths hadn't been introduced before. I found size to be easier to distinguish, but saturation fit the game metaphor better somehow.

The visualization techniques depend a lot on the background. If the color is strong enough so that transparency makes a big difference, then it is really helpful for making quick decisions. Otherwise, color saturation stands out more and is easier to process.
